MENINGITIS - SPAIN (03): LISTERIOSIS, RAW SOFT EWE CHEESE, PORTUGAL, RECALL, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
****************************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date Thu 8 Feb 2018
Source: Spanish Agency for Consumer Affairs, Food Safety and Nutrition (AECONSAN) [in Spanish, trans., edited]
http://www.aecosan.msssi.gob.es/AECOSAN/web/seguridad_alimentaria/ampliacion/quesos.htm


On [5 Feb 2018] the Spanish Agency for Consumer Affairs, Food Safety and Nutrition, through the Coordinated System of Rapid Information Exchange (SCIRI), learned of the existence of [a 39-year-old man; see 20180209.5618781] in the Community of Madrid affected by meningitis as a result of food intoxication by _Listeria monocytogenes_, presumably associated with the consumption of soft milk sheep cheese made by the company Ohian Txiki Koop located in the Basque Country. The affected [person is recovering] favorably.

The allegedly involved cheeses are the following: Gutizia, a raw sheep milk cheese; Txuria, a soft cheese from raw sheep milk; and Beltza, a lactic cheese-curl of raw sheep's milk.

The manufacturer has distributed these products to the autonomous communities of Madrid, Catalonia, and the Basque Country. As of [7 Feb 2018] there is evidence that there has been a small redistribution of a few units from Madrid to Andalusia, Castile-La Mancha, Castile and Leon, Extremadura, Galicia, Valencia, and Portugal.

The removal of all batches of raw soft-ewe sheep milk cheese is being carried out.

This information has been communicated through the national alert network to the competent authorities in the autonomous communities who are carrying out the appropriate actions, as well as to the competent Portuguese authorities through the European Rapid Alert System for Food and Feed.

As a precautionary measure, people who have any of these products at home are advised to refrain from consuming them. If they have consumed them and present any unusual symptoms, it is recommended that they go to a health center.

--
Communicated by:
Dr Irene Lai
International SOS
<irene.lai@internationalsos.com>

